{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3413546,"name":"Ashton Esler","username":"Cheez444","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/cheez444/{size}/213661_2.png","created_at":"2024-08-05T23:35:05.622Z","cooked":"<p>Our team has a kraken x60 powered swerve drive. Currently, all the code is configured to do is apply speeds to the swerve modules, but due to discrepancies in friction and whatnot, the robot does not maintain its heading while translating. We were wondering if any teams have corrections built into their code to help with this.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2024-08-05T23:35:05.622Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":24,"reads":118,"readers_count":117,"score":218.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":469561,"topic_slug":"swerve-rotational-drift-issues","display_username":"Ashton Esler","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":5}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63884,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"1912 Programming/Controls Lead"},"post_url":"/t/swerve-rotational-drift-issues/469561/1","custom_user_title":"1912 Programming/Controls Lead","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":5}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":5,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3413604,"name":"sam liu","username":"catrix","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/dbc845/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-08-06T02:26:45.826Z","cooked":"<p>If your robot has a gyro, you can have a <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> that holds the robot’s rotation still.</p>
<p>In your drive command, add three things:</p>
<ol>
<li>a <code>PIDController</code> that controls your robot’s heading <code>chassisRotationController</code>, <strong>remember to enable continuous input.</strong></li>
<li>a <code>wpilibj.Timer</code> that records the time elapsed after the previous rotational input from the pilot <code>previousRotationalInputTimer</code></li>
<li>a <code>Rotation2d</code> variable yielding the rotation <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> setpoint <code>rotationMaintenanceSetpoint</code></li>
</ol>
<p>now you can do a rotation maintenance:</p>
<ul>
<li>Whenever there <strong>IS</strong> a rotational input from the pilot, you reset the <code>previousRotationalInputTimer</code></li>
<li>Whenever <code>previousRotationalInputTimer</code> has elapsed 0.5 seconds,  the robot starts maintaining its current heading using the <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> controller.</li>
<li>Otherwise (when <code>previousRotationalInputTimer</code> has <strong>NOT</strong> elasped 0.5 seconds), execute the pilot’s rotational input speed and set the <code>rotationMaintenanceSetpoint</code> to the current robot facing.</li>
</ul>
<p>This way the robot will always try to stay in its current rotation if there is no rotational speed  input from the pilot.<br>
This is our implementation:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">
public class DriveCommand extends Command {
    private final DoubleSupplier driverXInputSupplier, driverYInputSupplier, driverRotationalInputSupplier;
    private final Drive drive;

    private final Timer previousRotationalInputTimer;
    private final PIDController chassisRotationController;
    private Rotation2d rotationMaintenanceSetpoint;

    public DriveCommand(DoubleSupplier driverXInputSupplier, DoubleSupplier driverYInputSupplier, DoubleSupplier driverRotationalInputSupplier, Drive drive) {
        this.driverXInputSupplier = driverXInputSupplier;
        this.driverYInputSupplier = driverYInputSupplier;
        this.driverRotationalInputSupplier = driverRotationalInputSupplier;
        this.previousRotationalInputTimer = new Timer();
        this.drive = drive;
        chassisRotationController = new PIDController(0, 0, 0); // fill your pid
        chassisRotationController.enableContinuousInput(0, Math.toRadians(360));
        super.addRequirements(drive);

    @Override
    public void initialize() {
        previousRotationalInputTimer.start();
        rotationMaintenanceSetpoint = drive.getPose().getRotation();
    }

    @Override
    public void execute() {
        /* apply deadbands */
        final double xInput = MathUtil.applyDeadband(driverXInputSupplier.getAsDouble(), 0.1),
                yInput = MathUtil.applyDeadband(driverYInputSupplier.getAsDouble(), 0.1),
                rotationInput = MathUtil.applyDeadband(driverRotationalInputSupplier.getAsDouble(), 0.1);

        /* reset rotation timer if there is rotation input */
        if (rotationInput != 0)
            previousRotationalInputTimer.reset();

        final double rotationSpeedOmega;
        /* no rotation input for 0.5 seconds, maintain current rotation */
        if (previousRotationalInputTimer.hasElapsed(0.5)) {
            rotationSpeedOmega = chassisRotationController.calculate(
                    drive.getPose().getRotation().getRadians(),
                    rotationMaintenanceSetpoint.getRadians());
        }
        /* there has been a rotation input within 0.5 seconds, reset rotation maintenance setpoint */
        else {
            rotationSpeedOmega = rotationInput;
            rotationMaintenanceSetpoint = drive.getPose().getRotation();
        }

        /* run chassis speeds */
        final ChassisSpeeds fieldRelativeSpeeds = new ChassisSpeeds(xInput, yInput, rotationSpeedOmega);
        drive.runChassisSpeeds(ChassisSpeeds.fromFieldRelativeSpeeds(
                fieldRelativeSpeeds, 
                drive.getPose().getRotation().minus(Constants.getCurrentAllianceDriverStationHeading())
        ));
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>And, just to remind you, if you are using vision to calibrate your robot’s pose, replace all the <code>drive.getPose().getRotation()</code> statements with <code>drive.getRawGyroRotation()</code>, which returns the gyro’s rotational reading directly, otherwise your chassis will be shaking a little bit.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2024-08-06T02:26:45.826Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":31,"reads":114,"readers_count":113,"score":207.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":469561,"topic_slug":"swerve-rotational-drift-issues","display_username":"sam liu","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60033,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"CE Student @ UWaterloo | 5516 Alum "},"post_url":"/t/swerve-rotational-drift-issues/469561/2","custom_user_title":"CE Student @ UWaterloo | 5516 Alum ","reactions":[{"id":"+1","type":"emoji","count":1},{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3414462,"name":"Ashton Esler","username":"Cheez444","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/cheez444/{size}/213661_2.png","created_at":"2024-08-10T16:29:34.856Z","cooked":"<p>It works but the rotation is delayed until after the robot stops translating. This may be a mechanical issue but we don’t understand why it’s happening.<